Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of cognitive radio for secondary access to spectrum and focuses on spectrum sensing techniques, specifically energy detection. This topic falls under the intersection of several computer science sub-disciplines, including information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), cryptography and security (cs.CR), systems and control (cs.SY), and multimedia (cs.MM). However, given the emphasis on wireless communication and signal processing, cs.IT and cs.NI are the most likely categories, followed by cs.CR, cs.SY, and cs.MM.
